Cook farro in 1 tablespoon oil in a heavy medium saucepan over medium heat, stirring, until lightly toasted, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in water and 1/4 teaspoon salt and simmer, uncovered, until just tender, about 15 minutes. Drain. Spread on a plate and cool completely. Whisk together lemon juice, zest, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and remaining 1/4 cup oil. Stir 2 tablespoon dressing into cooled farro. Slice mozzarella, then arrange over cucumber slices on plates and top with m√¢che and basil. Drizzle salads with remaining dressing and sprinkle with farro. Marimar Estate Don Miguel Vineyard '06